ing in flemington dot participated with the community events at flemington fields  she was a parishioner of st elizabeth ann seton roman catholic church in three bridges nj dorothy lovingly cared for her husband joseph for many years she was a devoted wife and they shared a special bond for  years dot raised four children and created a home that included her parents and welcomed her sister niece and nephew as a true extended family she had many friends and enjoyed socializing with those around her besides her parents dot was predeceased by her beloved husband of  years joseph a bongiorno on may   and two siblings john lessa and her beloved sister christine poiani dorothy is survived by four loving children joseph a bongiorno jr thomas f bongiorno and his wife susan janet higgins and nancy and her husband scott chamberlain  she will be deeply missed by seven cherished grandchildren lori bongiorno bethany bongiorno cristina nash alicia higgins elliot chamberlain sarah bongiorno and kathryn chamberlain an adored great grandson henry paul nash and a dear niece sheila piegaro and her daughter daniella piegaro relatives and friends are invited to attend a viewing at countryside funeral home  route  north three bridges nj  on monday june  from  pmand  pm and on tuesday june  from  am funeral services will be held on tuesday june  beginning  am at the funeral home followed by an  am funeral liturgy at st elizabeth ann seton roman catholic church in three bridges  committal words and entombment will follow at st magdalen cemetery in flemington  memorial contribution may be made in dorothy’s name to the st jude children’s research hospital memorial and honor program  north parkwaybox  memphis tn   to send condolences to the family or sign an online guest book please visit wwwcountrysidefuneralhomecom next rvcc testing center earns national recognition previous alexander farnham age  years of kingwood hunterdon insurance search for copyright  the hunterdon county news apprise 